1
00:00:49,299 --> 00:00:51,968
STILL SHINING

2
00:00:55,221 --> 00:01:01,019
JULY 2014

3
00:01:01,102 --> 00:01:03,313
MAEUM STUDY CENTER

4
00:01:03,396 --> 00:01:05,106
5:09 A.M.

5
00:01:13,114 --> 00:01:15,742
MAEUM STUDY CENTER

6
00:01:18,244 --> 00:01:23,833
MAEUM STUDY CENTER

7
00:01:27,462 --> 00:01:28,379
Hello.

8
00:01:32,675 --> 00:01:34,010
Hui-seo, you think can you walk?

9
00:01:35,220 --> 00:01:36,095
Yeah.

10
00:01:41,643 --> 00:01:42,894
Hui-seo, get on my back.

11
00:01:44,437 --> 00:01:46,606
Hui-seo, try to stand. You can do it.

12
00:01:46,689 --> 00:01:49,150
-Don't trouble your brother.
-Ma'am, it's fine.

13
00:01:51,861 --> 00:01:53,029
Hui-seo.

14
00:01:53,113 --> 00:01:55,573
Okay. One, two, three.

15
00:02:02,664 --> 00:02:04,040
Are you feeling okay?

16
00:02:11,923 --> 00:02:12,841
Sorry.

17
00:02:16,845 --> 00:02:17,887
You okay?

18
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:33,695
STILL SHINING

19
00:02:44,789 --> 00:02:45,915
You think you can you walk?

20
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:47,959
Goodness.

21
00:02:48,626 --> 00:02:50,378
Grandma, could you move back a bit?

22
00:02:50,962 --> 00:02:51,921
I'll come down.

23
00:02:52,839 --> 00:02:54,966
Come over here. He said he can manage.

24
00:03:00,972 --> 00:03:03,016
-I'm pretty good, right?
-Yes, well done.

25
00:03:03,099 --> 00:03:05,768
I told you I'm all better now.
You don't have to worry about me.

26
00:03:05,852 --> 00:03:07,562
I'm very proud of you.

27
00:03:08,688 --> 00:03:10,106
Goodness. Hi, Tae-seo.

28
00:03:10,857 --> 00:03:12,984
-It's good to see you.
-Have you been well?

29
00:03:13,067 --> 00:03:15,862
CONGRATULATIONS ON YOUR GRADUATION

30
00:03:19,449 --> 00:03:20,408
My medical report?

31
00:03:21,034 --> 00:03:23,411
You might not be ready for school
when classes start,

32
00:03:24,162 --> 00:03:25,204
so I'll submit it for you.

33
00:03:25,997 --> 00:03:27,999
I'm going to school, even if I'm hurt.

34
00:03:28,082 --> 00:03:30,043
You came all the way here for my sake.

35
00:03:30,126 --> 00:03:32,045
I'm not a kid. I can manage just fine.

36
00:03:33,129 --> 00:03:35,089
I can just take Bus 19 at the bus stop.

37
00:03:40,637 --> 00:03:42,138
Hey, the bus stop!

38
00:03:42,222 --> 00:03:43,139
Grandpa!

39
00:03:43,806 --> 00:03:45,433
Stop! Tae-seo's going to school.

40
00:03:47,936 --> 00:03:51,940
Right, your grandfather was worried
that Hui-seo would have trouble walking.

41
00:03:52,023 --> 00:03:55,026
He can walk fine on crutches,
and I'll go with him to and from school.

42
00:03:55,735 --> 00:03:57,987
I saw him playing soccer last summer.

43
00:03:58,655 --> 00:04:00,240
I also talked with your father.

44
00:04:01,282 --> 00:04:03,576
My parents both worked,

45
00:04:03,660 --> 00:04:05,578
so Hui-seo always came here
during vacation.

46
00:04:06,287 --> 00:04:08,289
Right. Well, you hang in there too.

47
00:04:09,207 --> 00:04:11,960
The local elementary school
closed last year,

48
00:04:12,043 --> 00:04:14,087
and there's been talk
about us closing too.

49
00:04:15,088 --> 00:04:17,090
But Hui-seo should be able to graduate.

50
00:04:17,715 --> 00:04:19,092
We don't get any transfers.

51
00:04:19,175 --> 00:04:20,885
You're the first in five years.

52
00:04:20,969 --> 00:04:21,970
I see.

53
00:04:22,053 --> 00:04:22,971
So…

54
00:04:23,554 --> 00:04:25,473
Did my documents and transcripts arrive?

55
00:04:26,182 --> 00:04:27,225
I'm looking for them now.

56
00:04:27,767 --> 00:04:28,935
Yes, they're all here.

57
00:04:29,936 --> 00:04:32,188
And I see
this is your second transfer this year.

58
00:04:33,231 --> 00:04:35,441
Why didn't you just come straight here?

59
00:04:35,525 --> 00:04:38,027
My aunt said
I had to go to college in Seoul.

60
00:04:38,111 --> 00:04:39,612
Living in Seoul won't guarantee that.

61
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:41,823
You didn't cause trouble there, right?

62
00:04:41,906 --> 00:04:43,199
No, of course not.

63
00:04:43,283 --> 00:04:45,618
Hui-seo found it hard adjusting to Seoul.

64
00:04:45,702 --> 00:04:46,703
Why?

65
00:04:47,704 --> 00:04:49,455
He was being bullied.

66
00:04:49,539 --> 00:04:53,042
God, those awful punks.
Doing that to someone who's hurt…

67
00:04:53,126 --> 00:04:56,379
I'll keep an eye on him,
so don't worry too much.

68
00:04:56,462 --> 00:05:01,301
With us, all the kids aiming for college
have transferred to schools in the city.

69
00:05:01,384 --> 00:05:04,220
The rest who remain here
help out with their family businesses,

70
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:05,972
so they have no pressure to study.

71
00:05:06,055 --> 00:05:10,059
Anyway, let's make sure
you get your high school diploma here.

72
00:05:11,394 --> 00:05:12,603
And no need to buy a uniform.

73
00:05:14,105 --> 00:05:16,274
We have some
that our graduates handed down.

74
00:05:16,357 --> 00:05:17,900
You should grab Hui-seo's as well.

75
00:05:17,984 --> 00:05:18,901
Okay.

76
00:05:19,610 --> 00:05:23,114
This one's for winter. The summer ones
are in front of the library upstairs.

77
00:05:23,656 --> 00:05:25,408
They're usually inside the library,

78
00:05:25,491 --> 00:05:26,826
but there's a kid named Mo Eun-a.

79
00:05:26,909 --> 00:05:29,537
She's doing independent study there,
so we moved them outside.

80
00:05:30,121 --> 00:05:31,873
She's the transfer from five years ago.

81
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:47,764
LIBRARY

82
00:06:17,627 --> 00:06:19,087
UNIFORM DONATION BOX (SUMMER)

83
00:06:26,969 --> 00:06:28,805
Hey, what on earth is this?

84
00:06:30,389 --> 00:06:32,100
It got crumpled in my bag.

85
00:06:32,183 --> 00:06:34,227
They're my mock exam scores
from March and June.

86
00:06:34,310 --> 00:06:36,312
I thought you may need them
for college counseling.

87
00:06:36,395 --> 00:06:38,856
No, the crumpling isn't the issue.
Look at this.

88
00:06:39,524 --> 00:06:41,859
Top-ranked student multiple times,
all 99s for grades,

89
00:06:41,943 --> 00:06:44,529
and in the highest percentile
in all major subjects.

90
00:06:44,612 --> 00:06:47,949
Geez, with these grades,
you can take your pick of med schools!

91
00:06:48,032 --> 00:06:51,494
You should have this framed,
not shoved into your bag.

92
00:06:52,829 --> 00:06:53,913
Gosh, you're…

93
00:06:58,167 --> 00:06:59,335
Gosh…

94
00:08:26,464 --> 00:08:28,174
Your desk didn't arrive.

95
00:08:28,257 --> 00:08:30,259
I told them a while ago.

96
00:08:31,552 --> 00:08:33,346
Goodness, what a mess.

97
00:08:37,308 --> 00:08:41,145
YEON CHANG-SIK

98
00:08:45,775 --> 00:08:46,901
Tae-seo's here.

99
00:08:48,361 --> 00:08:50,404
Gosh, good job finding your way here!

100
00:08:51,322 --> 00:08:52,865
But we have a problem.

101
00:08:52,949 --> 00:08:54,492
Your desk didn't arrive.

102
00:08:54,575 --> 00:08:55,743
I already told him.

103
00:08:56,744 --> 00:08:59,622
We should've made sure it arrived today.

104
00:09:00,706 --> 00:09:01,999
It's okay, Grandma.

105
00:09:02,583 --> 00:09:05,211
Right, I'll make sure
to tell them tomorrow.

106
00:09:05,294 --> 00:09:07,380
Why did you have to throw out
his father's desk?

107
00:09:09,423 --> 00:09:11,217
Why are you talking about his father?

108
00:09:11,300 --> 00:09:14,637
I'm just saying you could've thrown it out
after the new one came.

109
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:21,370
YEONWOO HIGH SCHOOL
CLASS 3-1

110
00:10:56,781 --> 00:10:59,950
The lights didn't even come on
since it's summer break, so I made a fuss.

111
00:11:00,743 --> 00:11:03,579
I heard they make you do independent study
until 10:00 p.m. in Seoul,

112
00:11:03,663 --> 00:11:06,040
so the least they could do
is help me study here.

113
00:11:06,791 --> 00:11:10,211
So now, just the library has power,
and I can use the fans.

114
00:11:12,672 --> 00:11:13,756
Turn that one on.

115
00:11:19,845 --> 00:11:21,097
Which bus did you take?

116
00:11:22,640 --> 00:11:23,682
The 6:12 a.m. bus.

117
00:11:24,558 --> 00:11:25,476
That's the first one.

118
00:11:29,355 --> 00:11:30,481
Sit wherever you like.

119
00:11:49,041 --> 00:11:50,876
You can switch into study mode right away?

120
00:11:53,337 --> 00:11:55,631
I need to warm up first. Don't mind me.

121
00:12:09,854 --> 00:12:10,896
Let me say one thing.

122
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:12,690
Just this. I promise.

123
00:12:14,233 --> 00:12:15,151
Go on.

124
00:12:16,986 --> 00:12:19,947
I suddenly have time
to spend on myself now.

125
00:12:20,990 --> 00:12:22,491
I was taking care of my dad…

126
00:12:25,202 --> 00:12:26,745
But I won't get into that.

127
00:12:27,788 --> 00:12:29,832
I just didn't want to waste this time,

128
00:12:29,915 --> 00:12:31,834
so I decided to study.

129
00:12:31,917 --> 00:12:34,962
I wasn't planning on going to college,
but I think I will.

130
00:12:35,671 --> 00:12:37,214
I don't know what I want to become,

131
00:12:37,298 --> 00:12:38,841
but I'll figure it out as I go.

132
00:12:39,758 --> 00:12:42,344
I know it won't change much,
but I'm giving it a go.

133
00:12:42,428 --> 00:12:45,222
What I mean is,
I was never big on studying.

134
00:12:49,059 --> 00:12:50,227
Just saying.

135
00:12:51,020 --> 00:12:51,937
Right.

136
00:12:52,563 --> 00:12:54,106
So my point was,

137
00:12:54,190 --> 00:12:55,900
that's why I need to warm up.

138
00:12:56,567 --> 00:12:57,818
I move around, so bear with me.

139
00:12:57,902 --> 00:12:59,487
Okay, do as you please.

140
00:13:06,285 --> 00:13:07,119
The Wi-Fi password.

141
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:09,872
I downloaded some online lectures,

142
00:13:09,955 --> 00:13:12,124
so I'll lend you my USB if you need them.

143
00:13:12,833 --> 00:13:13,751
I'm fine.

144
00:13:19,215 --> 00:13:21,884
Blue is for seniors, green for juniors,
and sophomores are…

145
00:13:22,635 --> 00:13:23,719
Maybe yellow?

146
00:13:25,846 --> 00:13:27,223
YEONWOO HIGH SCHOOL
MO EUN-A

147
00:13:34,063 --> 00:13:36,482
You're Yeon Tae-seo.
Hui-seo's older brother.

148
00:13:36,565 --> 00:13:38,025
We call your place "Hui-seo's."

149
00:14:03,092 --> 00:14:04,009
Sorry.

150
00:15:25,174 --> 00:15:27,301
The men's room is to the right.

151
00:15:48,656 --> 00:15:50,032
What about lunch?

152
00:15:55,496 --> 00:15:56,997
That's definitely gone bad.

153
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:08,759
TEACHERS' LOUNGE

154
00:16:09,635 --> 00:16:10,928
I'll restock the <i>ramyeon</i> I eat.

155
00:16:11,762 --> 00:16:15,015
Vacation's almost over anyway.
Two a day will last us just fine.

156
00:16:15,099 --> 00:16:18,018
I bought plenty in case anyone dropped by.

157
00:16:33,617 --> 00:16:34,618
For you and Hui-seo.

158
00:16:34,702 --> 00:16:37,329
Gym uniforms are valuable,
so upperclassmen never pass them on.

159
00:16:37,413 --> 00:16:38,956
They wear them forever.

160
00:16:39,039 --> 00:16:42,459
These are magic shorts.
They fit in middle school and as an adult.

161
00:16:43,335 --> 00:16:44,878
They always fit perfectly.

162
00:16:44,962 --> 00:16:47,089
It's amazing. They're so comfy too. Look!

163
00:16:47,172 --> 00:16:49,842
Hey! Come on, don't!

164
00:16:49,925 --> 00:16:51,010
You startled me.

165
00:16:52,469 --> 00:16:53,804
I'm just saying I'm wearing them.

166
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:56,890
Thanks for these.

167
00:17:02,438 --> 00:17:04,273
Your grandma's homemade kimchi.

168
00:17:05,482 --> 00:17:06,942
This is really special.

169
00:17:09,570 --> 00:17:11,030
When we were trading items,

170
00:17:11,113 --> 00:17:14,450
we gave Hui-seo his soccer cleats
for your sesame oil and perilla oil.

171
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:17,911
She thanked me every time she saw me
and then gave me a tub of kimchi.

172
00:17:17,995 --> 00:17:20,789
This kimchi is what my dad and I
treasure the most.

173
00:17:20,873 --> 00:17:22,082
Hui-seo's soccer cleats?

174
00:17:22,166 --> 00:17:23,792
Yeah, last fall.

175
00:17:23,876 --> 00:17:25,753
You were the one who bought them?

176
00:17:25,836 --> 00:17:27,588
I told you it was a trade.

177
00:17:27,671 --> 00:17:30,632
Your grandma would never know
what to get Hui-seo whenever he visited.

178
00:17:30,716 --> 00:17:34,845
The shoe bag and Park Ji-sung's jersey.
They were all my idea.

179
00:17:34,928 --> 00:17:37,389
She asks me for help every year.
Just for Hui-seo's gifts.

180
00:17:38,348 --> 00:17:39,725
She said you didn't want any.

181
00:17:43,103 --> 00:17:44,188
Eat up.

182
00:17:55,783 --> 00:17:57,409
Time to catch the bus.

183
00:17:58,869 --> 00:18:01,580
If you miss this one,
the next one comes in an hour and a half.

184
00:18:06,376 --> 00:18:07,461
Are you coming tomorrow?

185
00:18:07,544 --> 00:18:09,588
I'm in charge of opening
and closing the library.

186
00:18:09,671 --> 00:18:11,381
If you take the 6:50 bus, I'll be here--

187
00:18:11,465 --> 00:18:12,591
Don't worry about me.

188
00:18:15,511 --> 00:18:18,430
I don't know if I'm coming tomorrow yet,
so don't worry about me.

189
00:18:20,182 --> 00:18:21,100
Fine.

190
00:18:28,482 --> 00:18:29,399
Aren't you going?

191
00:18:30,150 --> 00:18:31,068
I came on my bike.

192
00:18:34,571 --> 00:18:36,490
I waited so I could tell you the bus time.

193
00:18:50,129 --> 00:18:51,672
Run! You'll miss the bus.

194
00:18:52,881 --> 00:18:54,716
You can see fireflies even in the fall!

195
00:19:08,522 --> 00:19:11,108
<i>Hui-seo, I'm cold. Let's go home.</i>

196
00:19:11,984 --> 00:19:13,527
<i>Yeon Hui-seo, listen to your mother.</i>

197
00:19:15,195 --> 00:19:16,572
We're going on ahead.

198
00:19:18,824 --> 00:19:22,286
Come on!
That bug's not around in the fall.

199
00:19:23,370 --> 00:19:25,455
They all die after the summer.

200
00:19:25,539 --> 00:19:26,373
Hurry up.

201
00:19:27,291 --> 00:19:28,750
Hey, it's a firefly!

202
00:19:30,043 --> 00:19:31,420
Where?

203
00:19:32,462 --> 00:19:33,964
Hey, it really is a firefly!

204
00:19:35,757 --> 00:19:38,468
There's so many! Grab them!

205
00:19:38,552 --> 00:19:39,511
Dad!

206
00:19:39,595 --> 00:19:43,265
-Where's Hui-seo? Isn't he coming?
-I don't know. He's catching fireflies.

207
00:19:43,891 --> 00:19:46,059
We grew up eating fireflies
back in the day.

208
00:19:46,143 --> 00:19:47,603
-Seriously?
-You're lying.

209
00:19:47,686 --> 00:19:50,272
-You ate them?
-Eating a firefly makes you electric.

210
00:19:50,355 --> 00:19:51,273
Don't be silly.

211
00:19:51,356 --> 00:19:53,150
-Dad is so unfunny.
-Yeah.

212
00:20:24,765 --> 00:20:26,808
Does your grandpa not know
how big you are now?

213
00:20:26,892 --> 00:20:28,769
He really is clueless.

214
00:20:29,561 --> 00:20:31,605
It's okay.

215
00:20:31,688 --> 00:20:32,856
It's nice and sturdy.

216
00:20:32,940 --> 00:20:35,067
Tae-seo can study anywhere.

217
00:20:35,150 --> 00:20:36,860
As long as he can sit, it's fine.

218
00:20:36,944 --> 00:20:38,612
Did you walk a bit today?

219
00:20:38,695 --> 00:20:40,155
Of course.

220
00:20:40,239 --> 00:20:44,076
I'm fine. Look. I'll be flying around
once the cast comes off.

221
00:20:44,159 --> 00:20:45,118
Just you wait and see.

222
00:20:45,702 --> 00:20:48,914
What should I pack for your lunch
to take to school tomorrow?

223
00:20:48,997 --> 00:20:51,667
He's not going to school, Grandma.
He has a desk now.

224
00:20:53,001 --> 00:20:55,254
I want <i>bibim-guksu</i> for lunch tomorrow.

225
00:20:55,337 --> 00:20:57,214
-Sounds great.
-I'm craving it.

226
00:21:20,862 --> 00:21:22,406
This is a bit hard to open.

227
00:21:25,534 --> 00:21:28,495
-Did you see me last Chuseok?
-I saw you every year.

228
00:21:28,578 --> 00:21:31,248
You stopped coming
in the summer after eighth grade.

229
00:21:32,457 --> 00:21:35,585
Even during Chuseok, you only stayed
briefly because you had to study.

230
00:21:37,004 --> 00:21:39,423
What happened? You acted like
you weren't coming today.

231
00:21:39,506 --> 00:21:41,091
I have to study.

232
00:21:43,468 --> 00:21:45,053
Since when have you known me?

233
00:21:45,804 --> 00:21:49,182
I moved here five years ago, so since
your last summer visit five years ago.

234
00:21:50,642 --> 00:21:52,269
Why the sudden interest?

235
00:21:54,187 --> 00:21:56,606
So you were nice to me
because you knew me.

236
00:21:57,941 --> 00:21:59,735
I'm just saying that I get it now.

237
00:22:03,572 --> 00:22:06,450
If you pick a spot and hide the key,
I'll open up if I arrive early.

238
00:22:07,576 --> 00:22:08,535
No.

239
00:22:08,618 --> 00:22:11,872
The school entrusted it to me,
so I need to open and close up.

240
00:22:11,955 --> 00:22:14,207
You can show up whenever and just study.

241
00:22:14,291 --> 00:22:15,917
The key is my responsibility.

242
00:22:19,129 --> 00:22:20,255
What?

243
00:22:21,048 --> 00:22:22,299
I didn't say anything.

244
00:22:26,053 --> 00:22:28,847
You don't have to know someone
to be nice to them.

245
00:22:28,930 --> 00:22:30,307
We're both just country kids here.

246
00:22:35,812 --> 00:22:37,856
It's going to be another hot day today.

247
00:23:08,303 --> 00:23:09,387
Do you want to use this?

248
00:23:10,764 --> 00:23:12,474
Yeah, thanks.

249
00:23:35,455 --> 00:23:37,249
-What?
-What?

250
00:23:39,042 --> 00:23:40,168
It looks good on you.

251
00:23:49,177 --> 00:23:50,971
Where's your bike?

252
00:23:51,054 --> 00:23:52,180
I took the bus today.

253
00:23:52,764 --> 00:23:54,015
I brought my bike today.

254
00:23:55,725 --> 00:23:58,728
Well, I just thought I'd ride with you
and get a little exercise.

255
00:24:00,730 --> 00:24:01,815
Then, go exercise.

256
00:24:37,601 --> 00:24:38,685
I'm getting off.

257
00:24:55,994 --> 00:24:59,206
Sir, quickly! Hurry!

258
00:25:49,798 --> 00:25:51,091
I'm not getting on.

259
00:25:51,174 --> 00:25:52,842
Don't you dare try to give me a ride.

260
00:26:02,018 --> 00:26:03,228
Are you serious?

261
00:27:09,461 --> 00:27:10,378
What's wrong?

262
00:27:32,150 --> 00:27:34,569
-The weather's nice.
-Yeah.

263
00:27:37,989 --> 00:27:39,115
Are you getting tired?

264
00:27:39,699 --> 00:27:40,533
No.

265
00:27:41,618 --> 00:27:42,452
Are you hot?

266
00:27:43,161 --> 00:27:44,162
No.

267
00:27:45,288 --> 00:27:46,539
Do you want to eat ice cream?

268
00:27:46,623 --> 00:27:47,457
No.

269
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:49,834
Yeah.

270
00:28:18,655 --> 00:28:19,864
Try throwing it farther.

271
00:28:27,455 --> 00:28:28,790
Hey, the bus is coming.

272
00:28:30,208 --> 00:28:31,626
Your bag!

273
00:28:32,210 --> 00:28:33,461
Your bag.

274
00:28:48,351 --> 00:28:52,689
MO EUN-A

275
00:28:53,857 --> 00:28:54,983
YEON TAE-SEO

276
00:29:11,166 --> 00:29:12,584
It's really hot.

277
00:29:36,649 --> 00:29:37,734
Hello.

278
00:30:00,340 --> 00:30:02,842
<i>-Husik.</i>
<i>-Husik?</i>

279
00:30:06,012 --> 00:30:07,472
That name doesn't feel right.

280
00:30:07,555 --> 00:30:09,140
<i>Chal-oksusu.</i>

281
00:30:09,224 --> 00:30:11,935
<i>-Chal-oksoso.</i>
<i>-Oksusu.</i>

282
00:30:12,018 --> 00:30:14,270
<i>-Oksosu?</i>
<i>-Susu.</i>

283
00:30:14,354 --> 00:30:16,481
<i>-Susu.</i>
<i>-Oksusu.</i>

284
00:30:16,564 --> 00:30:18,483
<i>Oksusu.</i>

285
00:30:32,997 --> 00:30:35,041
Thanks for making dinner.

286
00:30:35,124 --> 00:30:36,543
Sure thing. Eat up.

287
00:30:38,044 --> 00:30:39,337
Did So-hyeon leave?

288
00:30:40,672 --> 00:30:43,550
Yeah, she went to Seoul
with the guests from Hawaii.

289
00:30:47,053 --> 00:30:48,763
You were drinking, weren't you?

290
00:30:50,139 --> 00:30:51,558
That's why I feel great.

291
00:30:53,101 --> 00:30:55,270
And then you'll feel worse tomorrow.

292
00:30:56,104 --> 00:30:58,314
No, I'll be fine.
You just focus on studying.

293
00:31:00,233 --> 00:31:02,694
Exactly. That's what
dads are supposed to do.

294
00:31:02,777 --> 00:31:04,696
Tell their children
to just study all the time.

295
00:31:04,779 --> 00:31:07,323
It feels great
that I finally get to hear that now.

296
00:31:08,533 --> 00:31:10,785
"What's the point of all that?
Just take it easy."

297
00:31:10,869 --> 00:31:12,328
That's what you always used to say.

298
00:31:14,372 --> 00:31:15,999
Just live freely.

299
00:31:16,082 --> 00:31:20,295
Try living in different countries
and search for what you want to do.

300
00:31:20,920 --> 00:31:22,255
As if you're on a journey.

301
00:31:28,595 --> 00:31:29,429
Dad.

302
00:31:29,512 --> 00:31:33,391
I've been watching this kid who's been
through a lot but is pushing forward.

303
00:31:34,350 --> 00:31:35,602
It's really moving.

304
00:31:36,311 --> 00:31:38,021
-Someone your age?
-Yeah.

305
00:31:38,813 --> 00:31:41,774
-What a great kid.
-You're great too.

306
00:31:41,858 --> 00:31:42,942
You got all better for me.

307
00:31:45,194 --> 00:31:46,112
All right,

308
00:31:46,195 --> 00:31:47,864
I'll become an even greater dad.

309
00:31:49,824 --> 00:31:50,950
Enough.

310
00:31:55,496 --> 00:31:56,414
All right, I'll stop.

311
00:31:57,665 --> 00:31:58,917
I need to be a great dad.

312
00:32:35,912 --> 00:32:36,746
Mom…

313
00:32:41,334 --> 00:32:42,377
Mom.

314
00:33:05,400 --> 00:33:06,901
Any reservations today?

315
00:33:08,861 --> 00:33:09,696
No.

316
00:33:12,073 --> 00:33:13,741
I guess no energy either.

317
00:33:13,825 --> 00:33:18,079
Your stomach's probably empty,
so take this with the stomach medicine.

318
00:33:19,706 --> 00:33:22,834
I'm just feeling a little weak
because I threw up this morning.

319
00:33:27,130 --> 00:33:29,173
Go to school. Go study.

320
00:33:31,926 --> 00:33:34,554
Just give me five minutes, Dad.
Take the medicine.

321
00:33:34,637 --> 00:33:35,555
Okay?

322
00:33:51,863 --> 00:33:53,031
Yeon Tae-seo!

323
00:34:05,877 --> 00:34:06,961
Here.

324
00:34:07,670 --> 00:34:10,548
-Aren't you coming to school?
-I will. Wait for me.

325
00:34:29,984 --> 00:34:32,570
Dad? Dad!

326
00:34:33,780 --> 00:34:34,947
Dad?

327
00:34:38,618 --> 00:34:39,702
Dad!

328
00:36:00,992 --> 00:36:02,160
Nothing bad happened.

329
00:36:02,243 --> 00:36:04,078
I just freaked out for no reason.

330
00:36:05,580 --> 00:36:06,581
I can't hear you.

331
00:36:08,332 --> 00:36:09,709
Sometimes I can't hear your voice.

332
00:36:09,792 --> 00:36:11,836
Tell me what you just said.

333
00:36:14,338 --> 00:36:17,466
I was acting stupid,
but now, I feel calmer after seeing you.

334
00:36:17,550 --> 00:36:20,553
Seeing you makes me feel at ease.

335
00:37:03,471 --> 00:37:05,932
<i>So-hyeon, what time are you coming today?</i>

336
00:37:15,107 --> 00:37:16,400
<i>I won't be coming today.</i>

337
00:37:24,617 --> 00:37:25,493
Look at me.

338
00:37:28,663 --> 00:37:29,580
Look.

339
00:37:29,664 --> 00:37:31,082
You said it helps.

340
00:37:44,095 --> 00:37:45,429
I know it helps.

341
00:37:46,013 --> 00:37:47,723
But I need to go home right now.

342
00:37:48,516 --> 00:37:50,768
I'll only get in the way
of your studying like this.

343
00:37:50,851 --> 00:37:51,894
It's not good for you.

344
00:37:55,940 --> 00:37:57,233
No, don't.

345
00:38:05,074 --> 00:38:06,575
Go back to studying.

346
00:38:45,114 --> 00:38:47,283
-Tae-seo! Goodness.
-Grandma.

347
00:38:47,366 --> 00:38:51,203
I came here to buy some mosquito coils.
Let's go home together.

348
00:38:51,287 --> 00:38:55,833
Goodness, who's this handsome young man?

349
00:38:55,916 --> 00:38:56,876
Hello.

350
00:38:58,252 --> 00:39:00,713
-Come eat with us. Come, come.
-All right.

351
00:39:00,796 --> 00:39:01,714
I'll carry that.

352
00:39:02,673 --> 00:39:04,258
Go say hello to everyone.

353
00:39:24,820 --> 00:39:26,447
LIBRARY

354
00:40:15,704 --> 00:40:16,789
Name tags?

355
00:40:20,376 --> 00:40:22,044
IM A-SOL
IM JI-SOL

356
00:40:28,134 --> 00:40:29,343
What are these?

357
00:40:37,810 --> 00:40:41,439
I guess it's true that kids in Seoul
say they like someone by giving name tags.

358
00:40:41,522 --> 00:40:44,316
When did they put those in there?
I had no idea.

359
00:40:44,400 --> 00:40:48,946
Im Ji-sol, Kim Eun-su, Im A-sol.
A lot of girls with the last name "Im."

360
00:40:50,698 --> 00:40:51,615
I have no idea.

361
00:40:52,283 --> 00:40:53,200
No idea about what?

362
00:40:54,910 --> 00:40:55,911
Who's the prettiest?

363
00:40:57,163 --> 00:40:58,205
I don't know.

364
00:40:58,873 --> 00:41:02,084
I know who Im Ji-sol is,
but Hyeong-seok's the one who liked her.

365
00:41:02,168 --> 00:41:03,586
So you do know.

366
00:41:03,669 --> 00:41:06,422
Well, she was pretty famous.
She did well in school.

367
00:41:06,505 --> 00:41:07,423
So?

368
00:41:08,924 --> 00:41:09,758
I have no idea.

369
00:41:13,387 --> 00:41:15,556
-This is bad.
-What is?

370
00:41:16,307 --> 00:41:19,143
It's stuck in my head.

371
00:41:19,226 --> 00:41:20,811
I memorized their names.

372
00:41:22,021 --> 00:41:23,481
It's not like that.

373
00:41:23,564 --> 00:41:25,357
I really had no idea
they put those in there.

374
00:41:25,441 --> 00:41:26,609
How could you not know?

375
00:41:30,070 --> 00:41:31,363
When you're always tense,

376
00:41:32,031 --> 00:41:34,742
you only see and hear
what's right in front of you.

377
00:41:37,828 --> 00:41:39,330
Are you still tense right now?

378
00:41:42,458 --> 00:41:44,960
Just explain what happened yesterday.
I was really worried.

379
00:41:50,174 --> 00:41:52,885
I told you before
that I was taking care of my dad.

380
00:41:54,428 --> 00:41:56,138
He had severe depression.

381
00:41:56,889 --> 00:41:58,224
He even attempted suicide.

382
00:42:01,936 --> 00:42:05,105
When? Did you see it happen?

383
00:42:05,189 --> 00:42:06,565
I only saw him being taken away.

384
00:42:07,233 --> 00:42:09,610
He got divorced and left his job.

385
00:42:09,693 --> 00:42:12,029
We came nearby here on a trip.

386
00:42:12,112 --> 00:42:15,074
He fell in love with the marshes,
and we moved in five years ago.

387
00:42:15,783 --> 00:42:16,992
It happened that year.

388
00:42:17,910 --> 00:42:20,829
Ever since then,
I get really anxious when he's by himself.

389
00:42:22,540 --> 00:42:24,833
But he got a new job
just before summer break

390
00:42:24,917 --> 00:42:26,627
and also started seeing someone.

391
00:42:26,710 --> 00:42:28,546
If you ask me,
dating made a big difference.

392
00:42:28,629 --> 00:42:31,840
My dad told me to stop hovering around him
and go do what I want.

393
00:42:32,424 --> 00:42:34,760
Before that,
I hadn't even considered college.

394
00:42:34,843 --> 00:42:36,720
I was going to stay and help him out.

395
00:42:37,680 --> 00:42:38,806
So for the first time ever,

396
00:42:38,889 --> 00:42:42,184
I considered a different future
and started studying on my own.

397
00:42:43,269 --> 00:42:45,062
And then, Yeon Tae-seo appeared.

398
00:42:45,980 --> 00:42:47,189
The one Im A-sol likes.

399
00:42:49,692 --> 00:42:50,901
I'll stop. Sorry.

400
00:42:52,403 --> 00:42:53,529
Cut it out.

401
00:42:56,448 --> 00:43:00,786
Yesterday's situation happened
because my dad had changed, but I hadn't.

402
00:43:00,869 --> 00:43:02,830
My dad told me

403
00:43:03,747 --> 00:43:06,000
he thought he'd live with anxiety forever,

404
00:43:06,750 --> 00:43:09,545
but once he saw how trivial it really was,
the anxiety vanished.

405
00:43:11,088 --> 00:43:13,549
And that's exactly
what I experienced yesterday.

406
00:43:14,174 --> 00:43:16,135
I went home, and nothing had happened.

407
00:43:26,979 --> 00:43:29,106
I bet you're not considering
any local universities.

408
00:43:29,732 --> 00:43:31,358
And I'd never get into one in Seoul.

409
00:43:31,442 --> 00:43:32,443
We'll end up apart.

410
00:43:33,193 --> 00:43:35,446
-You're going to Seoul, right?
-Yeah.

411
00:43:36,196 --> 00:43:38,741
My grandparents and Hui-seo
are precious to me,

412
00:43:38,824 --> 00:43:40,534
so I want to help them from a distance.

413
00:43:41,327 --> 00:43:43,621
When I'm too close, I burn out easily.

414
00:43:47,082 --> 00:43:49,251
They're precious,
so you'll distance yourself…

415
00:43:50,794 --> 00:43:54,256
I never considered distance
when thinking about the future.

416
00:44:16,278 --> 00:44:17,488
It's different, right?

417
00:44:18,072 --> 00:44:19,948
It was still bright
at this hour yesterday.

418
00:44:22,076 --> 00:44:23,327
You'll be going to Seoul.

419
00:44:24,620 --> 00:44:27,289
Where will I be
and what will I be doing next summer?

420
00:44:28,290 --> 00:44:31,794
When I thought about the future
all through summer break,

421
00:44:33,462 --> 00:44:35,923
I'd feel good one moment
and then overwhelmed.

422
00:44:36,006 --> 00:44:38,384
Then, I'd feel excited and then down…

423
00:44:39,510 --> 00:44:41,887
What thoughts made you
feel good and excited?

424
00:44:43,472 --> 00:44:46,350
Working like a cool professional
while wearing an employee badge.

425
00:44:46,433 --> 00:44:47,267
What kind of work?

426
00:44:48,769 --> 00:44:50,354
It keeps changing.

427
00:44:50,437 --> 00:44:51,772
It's a teacher one moment

428
00:44:51,855 --> 00:44:55,442
and then something like a therapist
or even a regular office worker.

429
00:44:56,235 --> 00:44:59,321
A place with a lot of employees
and a fancy desk.

430
00:44:59,405 --> 00:45:00,781
I like being around people,

431
00:45:00,864 --> 00:45:03,117
so I'll take the elevator
up to the 30th or 40th floor.

432
00:45:03,200 --> 00:45:04,535
And we'll all pour out for lunch.

433
00:45:05,744 --> 00:45:08,872
That sounds like
it'd be a huge, competitive company.

434
00:45:11,375 --> 00:45:12,709
I'm pretty good at English, okay?

435
00:45:13,460 --> 00:45:14,628
And I draw vegetables well.

436
00:45:24,513 --> 00:45:26,390
Yeah, you're pretty good.

437
00:45:28,183 --> 00:45:30,936
I know. I'm not saying
this will get me into art school.

438
00:45:32,354 --> 00:45:34,064
But I'll keep looking.

439
00:45:34,898 --> 00:45:36,650
Whatever I do, I want to give it my all.

440
00:45:36,733 --> 00:45:39,403
My dad keeps telling me
to just take it easy and live freely.

441
00:45:39,945 --> 00:45:40,988
But I don't want to.

442
00:45:41,071 --> 00:45:43,282
I'm going to hustle and give it my all.

443
00:45:48,245 --> 00:45:49,246
You?

444
00:45:49,746 --> 00:45:52,666
Hui-seo would always boast
and say you'd go to med school.

445
00:45:52,749 --> 00:45:54,877
That's what you aim for
if you want to study hard.

446
00:45:57,754 --> 00:46:01,216
I only did it to reassure my parents
who were living paycheck to paycheck.

447
00:46:02,050 --> 00:46:03,510
But now, I just feel restless.

448
00:46:03,594 --> 00:46:05,554
I just want to find a job
and start making money.

449
00:46:07,055 --> 00:46:09,600
I'll think about how to live my life
after that happens.

450
00:46:09,683 --> 00:46:13,187
Is it really possible
to think about it afterwards?

451
00:46:14,521 --> 00:46:16,607
If I focus on doing
what I can do right now,

452
00:46:16,690 --> 00:46:18,275
I'm sure I'll end up somewhere.

453
00:46:20,110 --> 00:46:21,445
You sound like a grown-up.

454
00:46:22,571 --> 00:46:25,407
Yeah, right.
I don't even have an ID card yet.

455
00:46:25,491 --> 00:46:27,367
You'll succeed no matter what you do.

456
00:46:28,035 --> 00:46:30,120
You're different from the rest.

457
00:46:30,204 --> 00:46:31,330
I just seem different.

458
00:46:32,122 --> 00:46:33,040
This was special.

459
00:46:35,959 --> 00:46:37,044
I mean our situation.

460
00:46:37,669 --> 00:46:40,088
It was just the two of us
studying in this huge school.

461
00:46:49,056 --> 00:46:50,265
You like people,

462
00:46:50,349 --> 00:46:52,809
you're good at English,
and you draw vegetables well.

463
00:46:52,893 --> 00:46:55,270
I know there's a job out there
you can give your all to.

464
00:46:57,564 --> 00:46:58,649
It'll work out

465
00:46:59,358 --> 00:47:00,859
in ways we never imagined.

466
00:47:03,153 --> 00:47:06,865
We'll know for sure what that is
once we become adults.

467
00:47:14,164 --> 00:47:16,833
Where we'll be, what we'll do,
and with who…

468
00:47:23,382 --> 00:47:25,717
It feels like we've been
studying together all summer,

469
00:47:25,801 --> 00:47:26,969
but it's barely been a month.

470
00:47:27,052 --> 00:47:29,012
It was really nice studying with you.

471
00:47:29,096 --> 00:47:31,848
I felt more motivated
having someone else with me.

472
00:47:31,932 --> 00:47:33,392
I guess I like you.

473
00:47:44,736 --> 00:47:45,821
I'm all packed.

474
00:49:33,512 --> 00:49:34,763
It's been forever!

475
00:49:35,764 --> 00:49:37,265
I want to go home!

476
00:49:57,536 --> 00:49:58,370
Slow down.

477
00:49:58,954 --> 00:50:01,164
Hey, Kim Ji-min. Don't run!

478
00:50:01,957 --> 00:50:04,209
We don't offer physics
or a second foreign language,

479
00:50:04,292 --> 00:50:05,836
so you can study on your own.

480
00:50:06,795 --> 00:50:08,755
Just spend the day
studying at your own pace.

481
00:50:09,631 --> 00:50:10,882
Thank you, sir.

482
00:50:29,526 --> 00:50:31,570
MO EUN-A

483
00:50:42,247 --> 00:50:43,582
Want to play basketball later?

484
00:50:43,665 --> 00:50:44,791
-What do you say?
-For a bet?

485
00:51:00,098 --> 00:51:06,313
SEPTEMBER

486
00:51:06,396 --> 00:51:07,314
<i>You're walking great.</i>

487
00:51:08,064 --> 00:51:09,274
Your Achilles is fully healed.

488
00:51:12,402 --> 00:51:14,738
Grandpa's waiting outside,
so take your time.

489
00:51:18,784 --> 00:51:20,535
Walking like this without a cast

490
00:51:21,453 --> 00:51:22,662
makes it feel real.

491
00:51:26,833 --> 00:51:28,293
I'm stuck like this for life, right?

492
00:51:30,045 --> 00:51:31,171
I'm scared, Tae-seo.

493
00:51:46,353 --> 00:51:48,021
My right leg's fine, so I can do it all.

494
00:51:48,104 --> 00:51:52,108
The doctor also said
this is nothing to worry about.

495
00:51:52,192 --> 00:51:54,361
-Right, Tae-seo?
-Yeah.

496
00:51:56,071 --> 00:51:59,699
When I'm all grown,
I'll be able to drive tractors and stuff.

497
00:52:12,921 --> 00:52:16,675
I might be able to get rid of
the crutches soon.

498
00:52:16,758 --> 00:52:17,926
When I was walking earlier…

499
00:52:18,009 --> 00:52:21,847
OCTOBER

500
00:52:22,973 --> 00:52:24,850
<i>Ladies and gentlemen.</i>

501
00:52:24,933 --> 00:52:26,560
<i>We will shortly arrive at Cheongnyangni…</i>

502
00:52:26,643 --> 00:52:29,104
We're almost at Seoul.
Let's wait at the door.

503
00:52:33,817 --> 00:52:34,985
Gosh, I'm sorry.

504
00:52:52,377 --> 00:52:54,045
You didn't look back even once.

505
00:52:58,091 --> 00:52:59,926
-Where are you headed?
-Where you're going.

506
00:53:00,510 --> 00:53:03,221
I heard you got excused
to go to a college admissions seminar.

507
00:53:03,305 --> 00:53:05,056
I told them I was going as well.

508
00:53:07,726 --> 00:53:10,020
It feels like I haven't seen you in ages.

509
00:53:11,021 --> 00:53:12,147
I'm taking the subway.

510
00:53:13,356 --> 00:53:14,566
I'm on a tight schedule.

511
00:53:14,649 --> 00:53:16,735
I'm taking the subway too. What line?

512
00:53:16,818 --> 00:53:19,029
-Line 2.
-Gangbyeon Station…

513
00:53:19,112 --> 00:53:21,114
Isn't that close to Children's Grand Park?

514
00:53:21,197 --> 00:53:23,783
I think I went there once with my mom.

515
00:53:23,867 --> 00:53:24,910
All kids do at that age.

516
00:53:27,120 --> 00:53:29,664
But I don't know
if it really happened or if I imagined it.

517
00:53:29,748 --> 00:53:31,750
I'm not here to have fun.

518
00:53:35,879 --> 00:53:37,714
What line are you taking?
Do you know the way?

519
00:53:37,797 --> 00:53:39,132
Busy Yeon Tae-seo.

520
00:53:40,800 --> 00:53:41,718
Get going, then.

521
00:53:55,941 --> 00:53:59,361
2015 HANGUK NATIONAL UNIVERSITY
ADMISSIONS INFORMATION SESSION

522
00:54:03,907 --> 00:54:05,408
I'm Yeon Tae-seo.

523
00:54:12,540 --> 00:54:14,000
<i>So-hyeon, it's me.</i>

524
00:54:14,084 --> 00:54:16,127
<i>I'm on the subway right now.</i>

525
00:54:16,211 --> 00:54:18,922
<i>You live near Isu Station, right?</i>

526
00:54:19,005 --> 00:54:19,923
<i>Can I come?</i>

527
00:54:22,842 --> 00:54:23,677
<i>Of course.</i>

528
00:54:23,760 --> 00:54:26,221
<i>But take your time. I'm on my way as well.</i>

529
00:54:26,846 --> 00:54:30,392
<i>Come to Unit 610 at Space Inn</i>
<i>on 17 Isujungang-ro.</i>

530
00:54:55,667 --> 00:54:57,002
-You're early.
-Yeah. Did you eat?

531
00:54:57,085 --> 00:54:57,919
Yeah.

532
00:55:02,215 --> 00:55:03,216
You're here.

533
00:55:05,802 --> 00:55:06,970
Who is he?

534
00:55:07,053 --> 00:55:08,179
Let's go inside.

535
00:55:11,057 --> 00:55:11,891
What's the matter?

536
00:55:11,975 --> 00:55:13,768
You're dating my dad.

537
00:55:17,814 --> 00:55:18,648
Eun-a.

538
00:55:18,732 --> 00:55:20,942
-What in the…
-You've got it wrong.

539
00:55:22,986 --> 00:55:25,530
-You said you liked my dad.
-Yes.

540
00:55:26,114 --> 00:55:28,450
Liking someone doesn't always mean
you can date them.

541
00:55:29,075 --> 00:55:30,118
What kind of crap is that?

542
00:55:32,162 --> 00:55:34,998
Your dad won't date anyone.

543
00:55:36,583 --> 00:55:38,376
He's not interested in me.

544
00:55:45,675 --> 00:55:48,011
HANGUK NATIONAL UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

545
00:55:54,684 --> 00:55:55,643
You're all done.

546
00:55:55,727 --> 00:55:57,771
The results will be ready in an hour.

547
00:55:57,854 --> 00:55:58,938
You can come out now.

548
00:56:00,523 --> 00:56:06,696
MAEUM STUDY CENTER

549
00:56:10,450 --> 00:56:12,327
Hurry and give it. I have to go back now.

550
00:56:12,410 --> 00:56:14,329
Geez, you heartless punk.

551
00:56:14,829 --> 00:56:16,956
How did our teacher know
you were in Seoul?

552
00:56:17,749 --> 00:56:19,125
He booked a seminar for me.

553
00:56:19,751 --> 00:56:21,419
You're always getting special treatment.

554
00:56:22,545 --> 00:56:24,172
I heard your mock exam score dipped.

555
00:56:24,255 --> 00:56:26,508
-He said this might cheer you up.
-What is it?

556
00:56:34,849 --> 00:56:39,437
FAMILY BACKGROUND SURVEY

557
00:56:42,065 --> 00:56:43,608
PARENTS' DESIRED CAREER PATH FOR CHILD

558
00:56:43,691 --> 00:56:45,360
<i>"Something safe and peaceful</i>

559
00:56:46,444 --> 00:56:49,864
<i>where he can make a living</i>
<i>without struggle."</i>

560
00:56:55,120 --> 00:56:57,163
<i>There's no damage to the eardrum.</i>

561
00:56:57,789 --> 00:57:00,250
It's a temporary impairment
caused by exam stress,

562
00:57:00,333 --> 00:57:01,835
and your hearing may come and go.

563
00:57:02,460 --> 00:57:04,295
It should improve after the CSAT.

564
00:57:05,255 --> 00:57:07,382
When did the symptoms begin?

565
00:57:08,216 --> 00:57:10,885
March 3rd…

566
00:57:11,886 --> 00:57:13,721
That's right after starting
your senior year.

567
00:57:17,892 --> 00:57:19,352
No.

568
00:57:20,228 --> 00:57:21,062
So…

569
00:57:22,105 --> 00:57:25,108
It was after Hui-seo's entrance ceremony.

570
00:57:26,568 --> 00:57:29,696
They were going to buy him sneakers,
so Mom and Dad…

571
00:57:34,993 --> 00:57:36,161
They got in Dad's cab…

572
00:57:38,788 --> 00:57:40,623
and the three of them
got into an accident.

573
00:57:46,296 --> 00:57:47,672
My parents passed away,

574
00:57:49,132 --> 00:57:50,383
and Hui-seo's leg…

575
00:57:53,803 --> 00:57:55,096
His leg…

576
00:58:00,310 --> 00:58:01,186
Hui-seo's leg…

577
00:58:41,184 --> 00:58:45,188
TAE-SEO

578
00:58:45,271 --> 00:58:46,689
<i>The safety doors are closing.</i>

579
00:58:46,773 --> 00:58:49,317
<i>-Are you still in Seoul?</i>
-I'm not here to have fun either.

580
00:58:51,319 --> 00:58:54,614
-Where are you?
<i>-It was a big leap for me.</i>

581
00:58:54,697 --> 00:58:56,282
<i>I didn't come here to have fun.</i>

582
00:58:56,908 --> 00:58:58,076
I tried distancing myself.

583
00:58:58,159 --> 00:59:00,328
I worked up the courage for the first time

584
00:59:01,538 --> 00:59:03,373
and tried stepping away from my dad.

585
00:59:04,457 --> 00:59:06,876
<i>I thought, "I might make it</i>
<i>if I follow Yeon Tae-seo."</i>

586
00:59:06,960 --> 00:59:09,420
I was able to come
because I thought I was going with you.

587
00:59:12,507 --> 00:59:13,550
Where are you?

588
00:59:17,220 --> 00:59:18,555
The stop after Isu Station.

589
00:59:19,264 --> 00:59:22,433
<i>-I have to get to Cheongnyangni Station.</i>
-Is it Dongjak Station?

590
00:59:24,769 --> 00:59:25,687
Yeah.

591
00:59:29,065 --> 00:59:30,191
<i>Dongjak Station…</i>

592
01:00:21,534 --> 01:00:22,535
The Hangang River.

593
01:00:23,161 --> 01:00:24,829
It's my first time seeing it.

594
01:00:26,539 --> 01:00:28,124
The Hangang River? Where?

595
01:00:29,500 --> 01:00:31,044
Over there. Look closely.

596
01:00:33,630 --> 01:00:34,714
I can't see anything.

597
01:00:40,762 --> 01:00:43,890
I'm seeing the Hangang River
for the first time with Yeon Tae-seo.

598
01:01:01,949 --> 01:01:02,909
What's your deal?

599
01:01:02,992 --> 01:01:04,619
You're completely different now.

600
01:01:05,536 --> 01:01:07,538
You acted like you'd never see me again.

601
01:01:07,622 --> 01:01:09,540
-Earlier, I was--
-Not just earlier.

602
01:01:09,624 --> 01:01:12,460
Ever since summer break ended,
you ignored me and avoided--

603
01:01:27,100 --> 01:01:28,601
The tension finally wore off.

604
01:01:31,229 --> 01:01:34,107
Today, just suddenly.

605
01:01:35,108 --> 01:01:36,234
I know that feeling.

606
01:01:36,859 --> 01:01:38,319
How it happens all of a sudden.

607
01:01:40,947 --> 01:01:44,701
I've felt sick since yesterday evening,
just thinking about leaving Yeonwoo.

608
01:01:45,493 --> 01:01:48,162
But the second I saw you
on the train earlier,

609
01:01:48,246 --> 01:01:51,082
all that anxiety disappeared suddenly.

610
01:01:52,917 --> 01:01:53,918
It's strange.

611
01:01:54,001 --> 01:01:58,840
I've been studying better because of you,
and my grades have improved a little too.

612
01:01:59,424 --> 01:02:00,717
I also worked up my courage.

613
01:02:03,386 --> 01:02:04,887
I wonder what you are to me.

614
01:02:15,815 --> 01:02:16,733
It's the word

615
01:02:17,942 --> 01:02:20,319
<i>you memorized all summer</i>
<i>while sighing the whole time.</i>

616
01:02:24,115 --> 01:02:24,949
Yeah.

617
01:02:25,575 --> 01:02:26,868
I know.

618
01:02:26,951 --> 01:02:28,745
I know it. Don't tell me.

619
01:02:34,625 --> 01:02:35,543
To make possible.

620
01:02:40,131 --> 01:02:41,299
That's what I am.

621
01:03:04,113 --> 01:03:05,031
We'll have to

622
01:03:06,866 --> 01:03:08,159
be together forever.

623
01:03:28,930 --> 01:03:29,806
Let's do that.

624
01:03:33,935 --> 01:03:34,769
Starting now.

625
01:03:54,747 --> 01:03:57,667
STILL SHINING

626
01:04:26,404 --> 01:04:28,406
Subtitle translation by: Hyesoo Lee

